          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724395913786-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>salmon fillet[s]</strong>, with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 9-10 min, turning once halfway, or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once cooked, carefully peel and discard the skin then flake the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>salmon</strong> gently with a fork and keep warm</p>",
